    {
      "id": "task-graph-summary-derivation",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Derivation Rules",
      "position": {
        "x": 620,
        "y": -220
      },
      "width": 440,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Derivation Rules\n\nWhen the target is a real task graph:\n\n- derive `goal` and `status` from the primary goal node\n- count `task` nodes for completed / total\n- count `open-question` nodes for answered / total\n\nThis should come from the node collection when possible, not from decorative copy.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
